<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-03-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-03-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="297" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d297">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">110.11 DU/3–3054</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Secretary of
                                State</hi><note n="1" xml:id="d297fn1">Memorandum directed to
                                    <persName corresp="#p_MLT1">Merchant</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_MAD1">MacArthur</persName>; copies sent to <persName corresp="#p_RWS1">Robertson</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_JUA1">Johnson</persName>.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" type="conversation-or-meeting-date" when="1954-03-30">March 30,
                                    1954</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_MSRM1">Makins</persName> asked me at
                                <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName>’s request how long I
                            expected to be at Geneva. I said I expected to be there only for the
                            first week. The Ambassador said he thought that <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> had hoped that he and I might be
                            there for a fortnight, so that “we might deal with the Indochina
                            matter”. I said I was very skeptical that Indochina would come up in a
                            serious way in the first fortnight; that I foresaw procedural
                            difficulties in this matter and was anxious myself, as I had indicated
                            at Berlin, to get back shortly.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_DJF1">JFD</persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>